  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "You are given an integer `N`. Your task is to print the first `N` numbers of the **Fibonacci series**.\nThe Fibonacci series is defined as:\n\nF(1)=0F(1) = 0F(1)=0\nF(2)=1F(2) = 1F(2)=1\nF(n)=F(n−1)+F(n−2)for&nbsp;all&nbsp;n&gt;2.F(n) = F(n-1) + F(n-2)\\quad\\text{for all }n &gt; 2.F(n)=F(n−1)+F(n−2)for&nbsp;all&nbsp;n&gt;2..\n\n\nPrint the series space separated on a single line.\n\nInput Format\n\nThe line of input contains a single integer `N`, the number of terms to print in the Fibonacci series.\n\n\nOutput Format\n\nPrint `N` space separated integers: the first `N` numbers in the Fibonacci series.",
    "constraints": [
      "1 <= T <= 10",
      "1 <= N <= 93",
      "All Fibonacci numbers fit in 64‑bit unsigned integer"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "First line contains T, the number of test cases. Each test case contains a single integer N, the number of terms of the Fibonacci series to print.",
    "outputFormat": "For each test case, print N space‑separated integers: the first N numbers of the Fibonacci series starting from 0. Print each test case's output on its own line.",
